{
  "stem": "21786.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then I-- when I moved to this loft, so I switched to transport-- transportation-- which was, I mean, a kind of commando, which occasionally went for supplies outside of the ghetto and brought supplies, or the train would come and we had to unload it very quickly, or we had to transfer all kinds of stuff which was seized from the Jews in the protectorate and transfer it somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 70
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It had the tremendous advantage that, simply, we were young, and we had access to any amount of food, and any amount, practically, any amount of clothing, also, which was very unusual.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were altogether in this about 60 people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The normal ration for a working person, working Jew, was between 800 and 900 calories.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For a nonworking Jew, less than 600 calories, which is just enough to die.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The young people took it much better.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Eva was working, for instance, in a home for young children.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And we were quite, relatively, well fed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the medical care was good for them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They all, with exception of enormously small quantity, they all died eventually, being transper-- transported to the east.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And we-- then in 1942, we have been, the whole families-- Eva's parents, my parents and me-- we have been in three different transports, and we succeeded to get ourself out.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But then, in December, again we were all in it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I simply said to Eva, it has no sense.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Eventually we have to go, so at least we'll go all together.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Her father came to Theresien from the prison, and so we went.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We left Theresien in December 22, 1943.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We didn't know exactly where we are going.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
